cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference this work, please cite as below."
title: "Post-hoc MHA→MLA Conversion on a Single GPU"
abstract: >-
  A from-scratch single-GPU inference engine for Qwen3 used as the validation
  harness for converting an existing MHA/GQA model (Qwen3-4B) to Multi-head
  Latent Attention (MLA) without retraining, via activation-aware SVD with a
  partial-RoPE split. Studies the joint Pareto of KV compression × speculative
  decoding acceptance × perplexity at a fixed 16 GB VRAM budget.
authors:
